data.enText: not afraid of people, and used to living with them

data.chText: 平淡无奇的；枯燥乏味的
这里的生活相当枯燥，与纽约形成对比。
data.enText: You'll find life here pretty tame after New York.
willing to do what other people ask

data.chText: 我的医生对我有求必应。我想要休一天假时，他总会给我开病假条。
data.enText: I have a tame doctor who'll always give me a sick note when I want a day off.
to make sth tame or easy to control

data.chText: 狮子永远不能被完全驯化。
data.enText: Lions can never be completely tamed.
She made strenuous efforts to tame her anger.

ex.enText: His job is to tame elephants.
Horses are easy to tame while tigers are hard to tame.
Emma tames lions for the circus.

ex.chText: 有些野兽是可以驯养的。
ex.enText: It is possible to domesticate some wild animals.

ex.chText: 他学会了驯养野羊以获取羊奶，甚至还驯养出一只鹦鹉作宠物。
ex.enText: He learned to domesticate goats for milk, and even a parrot for a pet.

synonyms.bx: 指驯养动物为人类做事，或使其作为宠物和人类生活在一起。

ex.chText: 警察训练警犬探查毒品。
ex.enText: The policemen trained their dogs to detect drugs.
I want to train my cat to roll over.

synonyms.bx: 指训练动物做某事或做出正确的举动。

tr: make fit for cultivation, domestic life, and service to humans
example: The horse was domesticated a long time ago
The wolf was tamed and evolved into the house dog
He tames lions for the circus

tr: adapt (a wild plant or unclaimed land) to the environment

example: The author finally tamed some of his potentially offensive statements
meek as a mouse"- Langston Hughe

tr: brought from wildness into a domesticated state

example: she was one of the tamest and most abject creatures imaginable with no will or power to act but as directed

value.def: A tame animal or bird is one that is not afraid of humans.

example.ex: The deer never became tame; they would run away if you approached them.
example.tran: 那些鹿一直没有被驯服：你一靠近，它们就跑开。

value.def: If you say that something or someone is tame, you are criticizing them for being weak and uninteresting, rather than forceful or shocking.

example.ex: Some of today's political demonstrations look rather tame...
example.tran: 如今有些政治游行显得毫无激情。

example.ex: The report was pretty tame stuff.
There was no excuse though when Thomas shot tamely wide from eight yards.
example.tran: 托马斯在 8 码外一脚软弱无力的射门将球打飞，这回的确是没什么借口可言。

value.def: If someone tames a wild animal or bird, they train it not to be afraid of humans and to do what they say.

example.ex: The Amazons were believed to have been the first to tame horses.
example.tran: 据说亚马孙人最先驯化了马。

value.tran: 驯化，驯服(野生动物或鸟)

value.def: If you tame someone or something that is dangerous, uncontrolled, or likely to cause trouble, you bring them under control.

example.ex: Two regiments of cavalry were called out to tame the crowds.
example.tran: 调集了两个装甲兵团去威慑、控制人群。
